{
  "_comment": "CARC Phase 1 soft-launch managed settings for Claude Code 2.1.x. Deploy to /etc/claude-code/managed-settings.json on the login nodes (discovery1/2, endeavour1/2) as mode 0644, root:root, alongside hooks/precheck.sh. Posture: disable bypass mode, enforce managed rules, wire the PreToolUse hook on every Bash/Write/Edit/Read call, hard-deny unambiguously-exfil-or-destruction calls (incl. writing ~/.ssh/authorized_keys), and force an un-skippable user prompt for edits to shell-init/credential files AND for reads of files that commonly hold secrets (~/.bashrc, shell history, ~/.aws/**, kubeconfig, ...). The hook adds the dynamic checks the static rules can't express: destroying/recursive-chmod-ing $HOME, the 'cd ~ && rm -rf *' escape hatch, and running real computation (mpirun, torchrun, deepspeed, jupyter lab, ollama serve, matlab -batch, nextflow run, python script.py, ...) on a shared login node — pushing users to 'salloc --partition=debug' / sbatch instead. No sandboxing in Phase 1 (bubblewrap not installed cluster-wide). Root-only destructive commands (mkfs, fdisk, shutdown, ...) are not listed — the OS already refuses them for non-root users.",

  "_comment_rev_2026_07_21": "Revision for Claude Code >= 2.1.210. (1) Removed dead Write(path) rules — file permission checks match only Edit(path)/Read(path), and Edit rules already cover the Write and NotebookEdit tools. Every removed Write rule had an identical Edit twin, so no coverage was lost; this only silences the startup warnings added in 2.1.210. (2) Changed /etc rules to //etc — a single leading slash anchors at the settings source directory (/etc/claude-code/), NOT the filesystem root, so the previous rules silently protected nothing. Verified empirically: Read(/etc/sudoers) fell through to a kernel EACCES instead of a rule denial, while the ~/ rules denied correctly. (3) Added Edit ask-rules for shell-init and credential paths that previously prompted on read but not on write (~/.bash_aliases, ~/.zlogin, ~/.Renviron, ~/.kube, ~/.azure, ~/.terraform.d, ~/.cache/huggingface).",

  "allowManagedPermissionRulesOnly": true,
  "allowManagedHooksOnly": true,

  "permissions": {
    "defaultMode": "default",
    "disableBypassPermissionsMode": "disable",

    "deny": [
      "Bash(sudo:*)",
      "Bash(sudo *:*)",
      "Bash(su:*)",
      "Bash(su *:*)",
      "Bash(chmod -R /:*)",
      "Bash(chmod -R / *:*)",
      "Bash(chown -R /:*)",
      "Bash(chown -R / *:*)",

      "Read(//etc/shadow)",
      "Read(//etc/gshadow)",
      "Read(//etc/sudoers)",
      "Read(//etc/sudoers.d/**)",

      "Read(~/.ssh/id_rsa)",
      "Read(~/.ssh/id_dsa)",
      "Read(~/.ssh/id_ecdsa)",
      "Read(~/.ssh/id_ed25519)",
      "Read(~/.ssh/id_ecdsa_sk)",
      "Read(~/.ssh/id_ed25519_sk)",
      "Read(~/.ssh/*_rsa)",
      "Read(~/.ssh/*_ed25519)",
      "Read(~/.ssh/*_ecdsa)",
      "Read(~/.ssh/*_dsa)",

      "Edit(~/.ssh/authorized_keys)",
      "Edit(~/.ssh/authorized_keys2)",

      "Read(~/.aws/credentials)",
      "Read(~/.config/gcloud/credentials*)",
      "Read(~/.config/gcloud/application_default_credentials.json)",
      "Read(~/.config/gcloud/access_tokens.db)",
      "Read(~/.config/gcloud/legacy_credentials/**)",

      "Read(~/.netrc)",
      "Read(~/.pgpass)",
      "Read(~/.git-credentials)",
